.SH NAME
distill-ai-version - Show version, commit, and build date.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdistill-ai version [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
version prints the build info one field per line:

.PP
version: 
  commit:  
  date:    

.PP
The values come from ldflags injected at build time by the
Makefile (and by goreleaser for tagged releases). In a 'go run'
or unstripped 'go build' invocation they default to dev / none /
unknown.

.PP
The top-level --version flag prints the same information as a
single human-readable line.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for version


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	Path to a TOML configuration file. Overrides automatic discovery (no project walk, no user config).


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdistill-ai(1)\fP


